                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:addr>jms-004N</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004N.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="linear and thunkable inverses">linear and thunkable inverses</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be a deductive system, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : A\vdash  B]]></fr:tex> be a morphism in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>. Then both the type of (linear, thunkable) <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004O.xml" title="inverses in a deductive system" addr="jms-004O" type="local">inverses</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a proposition.</html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
